  "prompt": "Can educational testing services (ETS) sponsor cap-exempt H-1B visa?",
  "response": "Yes, Educational Testing Service (ETS) **can** sponsor cap-exempt H-1B visas.\n\nHere's why:\n\n*   **Nonprofit Research Organization:** ETS is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization whose primary mission includes educational research.\n*   **Cap-Exempt H-1B Requirements:** One of the primary categories for cap-exempt H-1B sponsorship includes working at a qualifying nonprofit research organization.\n\n**Therefore, ETS, meeting the criteria as a nonprofit research organization, can sponsor H-1B visas that are exempt from the annual H-1B cap.**\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Job Role Alignment:** The position being sponsored must be related to ETS's research mission.  For example, a research scientist position would likely qualify, while a role primarily focused on marketing might not.\n*   **Meeting all H-1B Requirements:** Even though cap-exempt, the sponsored employee and the position must still meet all other H-1B requirements, such as holding the required degree and being paid the prevailing wage.\n\n**Disclaimer:**  Visa regulations and interpretations are subject to change. It's always best to consult directly with an immigration attorney or review the latest USCIS guidelines for the most up-to-date information.\n",
